<tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Tansu Penbe Çiller<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> (<tag name="MISC" value="start"/>Turkish<tag name="MISC" value="end"/> pronunciation:&#160; ; b. <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>October 23, 1944<tag name="DATE" value="end"/>, <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Istanbul<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/>) is a <tag name="MISC" value="start"/>Turkish<tag name="MISC" value="end"/> economist and politician. She was <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Turkey<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>'s first and only female Prime Minister.
She is the daughter of a <tag name="MISC" value="start"/>Turkish<tag name="MISC" value="end"/> governor of <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Bilecik<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/> province during the <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1950<tag name="DATE" value="end"/>s. She graduated from the School of Economics at <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Robert College<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> after finishing the <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>American College for Girls<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> in <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Istanbul<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/>. She received her M.S. from the <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>University of New Hampshire<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> and Ph.D. from the <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>University of Connecticut<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>. She later completed her postdoctoral studies at <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Yale University<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>. <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Çiller<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> taught economics at <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Franklin<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> and <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Marshall College<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> in <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Lancaster<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/>, <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Pennsylvania<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>. In <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1978<tag name="DATE" value="end"/>, she became a lecturer at <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Boaziçi University<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/> in <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Istanbul<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/> and in <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1983<tag name="DATE" value="end"/> she was appointed as professor by the same institution. She also worked in the now-defunct <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Istanbul Bank<tag name="ORGANIZATION" v